Super Eagles interim coach, Austin Eguavoen has admitted that SC Paderborn of Germany left back, Jamilu Collins encountered some difficulties in his travel itineraries before his arrival yesterday night. Collins was expected to have joined his teammates upon his release on January 3rd  but Eguavoen revealed that the defender could only join the squad  after the issues were sorted. ” We had some issues on his arrival but  we have sorted it out,” the former Torpedo Moscow star said at the Press Conference yesterday in Garoua. The Eagles interim boss also spoke about his relationship with the incoming Nigerian coach, Jose Peseiro.    Senegal, Morocco in good start     Rohr roots for Eagles against Pharaohs      Egypt’s Queiroz welcomes Nigeria tough challenge   - Advertisement -  “We are in touch. It’s not a problem. Mind you I am the Technical Director of Nigeria Football Federation, by extension and right ,  am his (Peseiro’s) boss.  “So collaboration is very good, because whatever we do here is to make it a soft landing and platform to operate.  “We want to be at the next World Cup,” he enthused.  “There is need to make everything comfortable and smooth for him. When Peseiro resumes, he can now add his own ideas.”